 :forward-model-takes
 [{:id :held-deferred-schema-story
   :status :prospective
   :anchored-under [:principled-deferral "general held/deferred schema"]
   :attested-by-existing-patterns []
   :seeded-by-nonexistent-patterns ["held-item-wake-trigger"
                                    "deferral-ledger-as-operator-memory"
                                    "deferred-work-reentry-protocol"]
   :story
   "If the held/deferred schema existed, every parked obligation would become a typed object with reason, owner, evidence condition, wake trigger, expiry/review rule, and downstream re-entry path."
   :what-we-get
   [{:gain :bounded-deferral-memory
     :description "Held work stops being folklore; every pause has a durable record and a named wake condition."}
    {:gain :operator-safe-reentry
     :description "The operator can ask 'what should wake up now?' without scanning old mission prose by hand."}
    {:gain :mission-pressure-signal
     :description "Repeated held items become evidence for new missions, invariants, or pattern-library entries."}
    {:gain :pattern-seeding-loop
     :description "The forward model can mint candidate patterns from repeated reason/trigger/outcome shapes."}]
   :candidate-patterns-to-seed
   [{:pattern "agent/held-item-wake-trigger"
     :definition "A held item is well formed only if it names the event, evidence, or date that wakes it back into work."}
    {:pattern "agent/deferral-ledger-as-operator-memory"
     :definition "Deferred obligations should live in a queryable ledger rather than in prose-only mission margins."}
    {:pattern "mission/deferred-work-reentry-protocol"
     :definition "When a held item wakes, it must re-enter through a declared mission phase or operator review gate rather than becoming an unscoped task."}]}]

