 :semilattice-next-plan
 {:status :not-yet-built
  :observation
  "The pattern library is a flat namespace of directories and flexiarg files; its cross-references give phylogeny and reuse history, but not by themselves the logical semilattice of stack capabilities."
  :measured-sources
  {:pattern-library {:path "futon3/library"
                     :top-level-directories 74
                     :flexiarg-files 1010}
   :vsatarcs-stories {:path "futon5a/holes/stories"
                      :aif-edn-files 52
                      :markdown-files 101}}
  :distinction
  {:phylogeny
   "Pattern-to-pattern cross-reference, reuse, and derivation: useful for lineage, but not enough to answer what capability depends on what."
   :logical-semilattice
   "Capability/support structure over stories, missions, invariants, patterns, and apparatus: enough to ask what is actually in the stack and what would change if a hole were filled."}
  :candidate-node-types
  [:capability :pattern :mission :story-claim :apparatus :hole :invariant :source-surface]
  :candidate-edge-types
  [:supports :instantiates :realized-by :warranted-by :pressured-by :closes
   :generalises-shape-to :depends-on :exposes-hole :seeds-pattern]
  :first-sources
  [{:source "VSATARCS AIF stories"
    :paths ["futon5a/holes/stories/*.aif.edn" "futon7a/vsatarcs.html"]
    :role "Provides existing logical/story edges such as :supports, :closes, :instantiates, :generalises-shape-to, and load-bearing conflicts."}
   {:source "pattern library"
    :paths ["futon3/library/**/*.flexiarg"]
    :role "Provides pattern vocabulary and cross-reference/lineage evidence; should become warrants, not the whole logical structure."}
   {:source "stereolithography mission"
    :paths ["futon5a/holes/missions/M-stack-stereolithography.md"]
    :role "Provides the capability-status discipline: :exists-already, :emerging, :declared, with evidence-backed claims only."}
   {:source "capability star map"
    :paths ["futon0/holes/missions/M-capability-star-map.md"
            "futon0/holes/missions/M-capability-star-map.graph.edn"
            "futon0/holes/missions/M-capability-star-map.ensemble.edn"
            "futon2/web/war-machine/resources/public/data/capability-star-map.graph.json"]
    :role "Provides the existing structure-view over capabilities: nodes, prerequisites, minted-by missions, and scheduler-facing graph shape."}
   {:source "invariant surfaces"
    :paths ["futon3c/docs/structural-law-inventory.sexp"
            "futon4/futon-stack-invariant-model.edn"]
    :role "Provides a backbone for operational/candidate capability rows."}]
  :related-mission-crossrefs
  [{:mission "M-capability-star-map"
    :path "futon0/holes/missions/M-capability-star-map.md"
    :why
    "Names the prior capability graph: intended capabilities, prerequisite edges, build order, and a granularity axis."}
   {:artifact "M-capability-star-map.graph.edn"
    :path "futon0/holes/missions/M-capability-star-map.graph.edn"
    :why
    "Concrete structure-view over capabilities, with satisfied/held status, grounding, minted-by missions, and scope/prerequisite edges."}
   {:artifact "C-pudding-prover §8.2"
    :path "futon7/holes/C-pudding-prover.md#8.2"
    :why
    "Records the split: Pudding Prover registry = status-view; M-capability-star-map = structure-view over the same capability set."}]
  :embedding-clustering-plan
  {:status :proposal
   :pattern-only
   "Pattern clustering can still help name warrant vocabularies and latent pattern families, but it is not required for the first upward cascade."
   :mission-only
   "Cluster mission embeddings independently to expose feature regions, because missions and capabilities are closer to the 'what is in the stack?' question than pattern-library lineage is."
   :mission-to-pattern-crossrefs
   "Use explicit mission→pattern references as direct warrants for each mission cluster. This concrete cited-pattern layer is stronger than both embedding proximity and pattern-cluster membership."
   :combined-view
   "A useful render should first show mission/feature clusters as capability basins and the concrete patterns actually cited inside each basin. Pattern clusters can then sit above those citations as optional warrant-constellation labels."
   :risk
   "A single joint embedding of missions and patterns may blur feature topology with method/warrant topology; run separate clusterings first, then join by explicit citations and high-confidence nearest neighbours."}
